text: Bolshiye Shidy () is a rural locality (a village) in Bashshidinsky Selsoviet, Nurimanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 456 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 6 km from Krasnaya Gorka, 55 km from Ufa. == References == Category:Rural localities in Nurimanovsky District
title: Bolshiye Shidy
